{
  "texts": [
    "One direct consequence of this is that users-especially students-who choose to use generative AI to produce writing may be unwittingly espousing perspectives and using voices that are very different from their own.",
    "Students may not even be aware of this fact, leading to a growing disconnect and the eventual atrophy of the ability to develop and articulate ideas in their own words.",
    "An LLMs' ability to produce content that reads as human has already led to concerns over plagiarism for instructors, and on a broader scale will likely lead to with trust and the reliability of digital writing.",
    "At a higher level, researchers are aware aligning LLMs with human preferences and values through RLHF \"rel[ies] on universal framings that obscure the question of which values the systems should capture and align with\" [17].",
    "Annotators inherently bring their own biases into their judgment of model responses, which may lead to situations where model outputs \"cater primarily to the preferences of a minority, lacking varied representation across cultures, races, or languages.\""
  ]
}